				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Line Up" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>The purpose of the game is to compose a hand of 11 &amp;quot;footballer&amp;quot; cards and lay them out on the table as if they were a football team, trying to obtain the highest combination value, and win the &amp;quot;championship&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The 104 &amp;quot;footballer&amp;quot; cards are divided into 4 roles: goalkeepers, defenders, midfielders and strickers; and each card (except for goalkeepers) has three values: left wing, centre and right wing.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the start every player draws 1 (from 6) &amp;quot;Line-up&amp;quot; card: this card shows the number of footballer for each role and their position on the field (left, centre, right).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A player's turn consists of the following phases: &amp;#10;1- draw 2 cards from the &amp;quot;footballer&amp;quot; pile, or take the top card from the discard pile&amp;#10;2- swap footballers with other players (not mandatory)&amp;#10;3- discard 1 card (only if the player drew 2 cards in phase 1)&amp;#10;Whenever a player has 11 cards in his hand at the end of the turn, he must declare it and from then on, he can only draw 1 card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When a player states that he wants to close, the other players have 1 turn to try to improve their team.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player who has lined up the team with the highest sum of the values of the footballer, is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
